The paper presents an I/O-efficient algorithm for computing similarity joins, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The algorithm is based on locality-sensitive hashing (LSH), which is a technique commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the time and I/O complexity of the algorithm, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.DM).
